# Checkpoint Persistence

After substantial work, update the project memory when any of these occur:

- A bug root cause is confirmed
- A migration is added
- A PR is merged
- Runtime behavior changes
- A major UI or status semantic changes
- A new architectural rule is established
- A meaningful next step is identified

## Write a structured entry (source of truth)

Create one file under:

`02 - Projects/GithubArchiver/entries/YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md`

(or `docs/ai-memory/seed/02 - Projects/GithubArchiver/entries/` when the vault is unavailable)

Every entry must start with YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
date: 2026-07-18
pr: 8
commit: abc1234
area:
  - search
  - daemon
type: architecture   # architecture | incident | migration | pr | debt
status: open         # merged | open | verified | superseded | open-debt
supersedes: null
title: Short headline
migration: null
---
```

Body: what / why / tests / remaining verification. No chat transcripts. No secrets.

Then regenerate indexes:

```bash
npm run memory:timeline
```

That refreshes `Timeline.md`, `Architecture Decisions.md`, `Production Incidents.md`, `Migrations.md`, `PR Timeline.md`, and `Open Technical Debt.md`.

Finally, refresh the hand-maintained live summary in `Current Status.md` (**Now** / open verification only).

Do not write speculative conclusions as facts.
